Preheat your oven to 200°c. Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, scoop out
the seeds. Chop it widthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm chunks (no need to
peel!). Chop each @beetroot{1} into 1cm chunks. Chop the @broccoli{1} into florets
(like small trees!).

Spread your butternut squash and beetroot on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with
@olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix. Spread them into a single
layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender and golden,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> TIP: Use 2 trays if you need to, your veg needs to be nicely spread out.

When the veg has 15 mins left, pop the @salmon fillets{2} on a lined baking tray with
the broccoli, drizzle over @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast
on the middle shelf of your oven until the broccoli is tender and the salmon cooked
through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when it is opaque in the middle.

== Tarragon Dressing ==

Pick the @tarragon{1/2}(leaves picked from stalks and roughly chopped) and roughly
chop (discard the stalks). In a #small bowl{}, combine the @honey{15}, @wholegrain
mustard{1}, @olive oil{1.5}(for the dressing) and tarragon. Mix well and season to
taste.

If you have a bit of spare time have a little tidy up or use it as an excuse to
relax.

Share the roasted squash and beetroot between your plates, pop the salmon on top and
serve the broccoli next to it. Then drizzle over the tarragon dressing. Enjoy!